Sheila D Yeah

BALTIMORE

Sheila D Yeah was born and raised in her hometown of Baltimore, MD. Sheila D.Yeah dropped her first EP entitled "Pretty Ratchet" featuring premiere singles "Ballin' Like I'm Diddy" and "We On" f/ Fat Trel in July 2011. Single "Ballin Like I'm Diddy" produced by W.R.A.B Mell introduced Sheila D. Yeah to the DMV area as a sassy, classy, witty & lyrical femcee. The video for "Ballin Like I'm Diddy" showing a versatile fly and sexy Sheila D. was released in early May 2011 with production by LiveFreeFilms. This Single, jump started Sheila D's career and got the attention of some big names including 'Charlamagne Tha God' from MTV's Guy Code, who went on to endorse Sheila D's smash hit. Charlamagne Tha God Endorses Sheila D Yeah Ballin' Like DIDDY!! Sheila D dropped her sophomore EP entitled "Simply Said" as a follow up to her premiere EP Pretty Ratchet. The EP features 12 tracks including singles "Rewind" and "Baltimore Dope" featuring Fat Trel. These tracks were featured on DMV and Baltimore Hip-hop/Music blogs along with interviews and reviews in local online magazines and lifestyle blogs Including Dope Music Blog, TheHipHopUpdate and DMV Heat . Sheila D Yeah has been performing in various states since her premiere single dropped. She's been featured on shows with Board of Administration artists Black Cobain and of course Fat Trel, She has headlined for Yo Gottiâs Road to Riches tour, performed at Dunk Xchange NYC, and various colleges in the DMV area. Sheila has also been featured on NYC's Power 105.1"The Breakfast Club" with Envy, Angela Yee and Charlamagne Tha God. Style- High fashion with a bit of edge
